text: J. Eugene Goddard (April 28, 1901 – December 18, 1979) was an American politician who served in the New York State Assembly from Monroe's 1st district from 1949 to 1964. He died of a heart attack on December 18, 1979, in Rochester, New York at age 78. ==References== Category:1901 births Category:1979 deaths Category:Members of the New York State Assembly Category:New York (state) Republicans Category:20th-century American politicians
